12/04/2005
BUCHAREST, Romania -- President Traian Basescu met with the ambassadors of EU member states on Monday (11 April) to discuss the European Parliament and its upcoming vote on the Accession Treaty for Romania and Bulgaria. 
Basescu said he believes parliament will greenlight accession during Wednesday's vote.
In other news, Basescu's spokeswoman said on Monday that the three Romanian journalists kidnapped in Iraq are alive and in good health. 
Omar Hayssam, a Romanian-Syrian businessman, was arrested in Bucharest last week on charges of complicity in the abduction. 
(Rompres, Nine o'clock, AFP - 11/04/05)
